In addition to these packages, the ViennaRNA 2.7.2 software package has to be installed in order to predict the structure and accessibility of the target mRNA. Retrieve the source code from their website and install the software by following the instructions in the README and INSTALL file accompanied with the Source Code download. 
https://www.tbi.univie.ac.at/RNA/ 
The ViennaRNA 2.7.2 package is a prediction model that is programmed to analyze RNA secondary structures, i.e. self-folding, accessibility of (for this case) ASO to the pre-mRNA/mRNA. 
The software isn't specifically incooperated into the R-script, but rather as a complementary software program downloaded into the source code of the computer. 


