From the ENSEMBL_ID, we can also assess potential single nucleotide polymorphisms, which may interfere in the affinity of the ASO binding potential -  frequent SNPs can therefore be found in the following code, and later on we may define restrictions as to how high of a frequency of SNPs at a selected site may be in the ASO prediction model. 

```{r}
PMs = getBM(attributes = c("minor_allele_freq",
                           "chromosome_start"),
            filters = "ensembl_gene_id",
            values = ensembl_ID,
            mart = martHS)%>%
  as_tibble() %>%
  arrange(chromosome_start,
          desc(minor_allele_freq)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(minor_allele_freq),
         !duplicated(chromosome_start)) %>%
  rename(chr_start=chromosome_start,
         PM_freq=minor_allele_freq)

```

Now that we have established the genomic coordinates of the pre-mRNA sequence, frequency of SNPs and compared its conservation in mice, we can integrate the ViennaRNA package. 
The first code below predicts the accessibility of the RNA target's pre-mRNA. This will generate the probabilities of which the ASO might bind to the pre-mRNA. 

```{r}
RNAplfold_R = function(seq.char, L.in = 40, W.in = 80, u.in = 16){
  cmmnd2 = paste("RNAplfold -L",L.in,"-W", W.in, "-u",u.in)
  seq.char = as.character(seq.char)
  cat(seq.char, file = paste("|", cmmnd2, sep = ""))
  acc.tx=read.delim("plfold_lunp", as.is = T, skip = 2,
                    header = F, row.names = 1)
  acc.tx = acc.tx[, colSums(is.na(acc.tx)) !=nrow(acc.tx)]
  colnames(acc.tx) = 1:ncol(acc.tx)
  file.remove("plfold_lunp")
  file.remove("plfold_dp.ps")
  return(acc.tx)
}
```

The next two ViennaRNA code (RNAduplex_R and RNAselffold_R) predicts the duplex formation, the binding kinetics between the ssDNA ASO and the pre-mRNA RNA target, and the possibility of the oligonucleotide self-folding onto itself.

```{r}
RNAduplex_R = function(seqs){
  sys_cmd = system('RNAduplex',input = c(seqs,seqs),
                   intern = TRUE)
  as.numeric(sapply(
strsplit(sys_cmd, "\\s+", perl = T), 
function(x){ gsub("\\(|\\)", "", tail(x, n=1) )
}))
}
```

```{r}
RNAselffold_R = function(seqs){
  output = system("RNAfold --noPS",input = c(seqs),
                  intern = T)
  output = unlist(strsplit(output[grepl("[0-9]", 
  output)], "[(]"))
  as.double(gsub(" |[)]", "", output[grepl("[0-9]",
output)]))
}


```

